tervetuloa

  • languages are pretty cool

basics

  • no articles
  • no gender
  • subject-verb-object
  • relativly normal tenses
  • plural you
  • plural it
  • question suffix
    • ko
  • or versus xor

noun cases

  • noun conjugation
  • yay

opening sentence to the usa foreign service institute’s 1968 classic, the finnish graded reader:

karhulla oli juustonpala suussa

the bear had a piece of cheese in its mouth

  • el oso tenía un trozo de queso en la boca
  • “the bear had a piece of cheese in its mouth”
  • 熊嘴里叼着一块奶酪
  • “bear mouth was holding a cheese”

technical stuff

vowel harmony

back vowels
a, o, u
front vowels
ä, ö, y
middle vowels
e, i

consonant gradation

some sounds only work as the final consonant in a word

  • mp -> mm
  • nt -> nn
  • lt -> ll

kirjakieli ja puhekieli

  • don’t conjugate verbs the same way
  • don’t use they
  • don’t use past tense
  • just ignore all the middle letters. they don’t matter
    • sinä -> sä, sää, sie, nää
  • some of the ending letters too
  • new question suffix
    • ks
